<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1468> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1468" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Placed in charge of the garrison at Brundisium by Laevinus (Liv. 24.40.5; see 215, Prefects; and Münzer, Gent. Val. 38, no. 16)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1394> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1394" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Marcellus at Nola (Liv. 23.16.13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1393> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1393" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The battle described in Livy was probably unimportant and the details, such as the number of the men lost, quite unreliable. Münzer (Gent. Val. 59, note 9) considers this Valerius a fictitious character taken from Valerius Antias. Lübker, no. 24, keeps the identification given above." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1292> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1292" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Cicero (Phil. 5.27) and Livy (21.6.8), these were sent to Saguntum to order Hannibal to desist from the siege. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 38, no. 16." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1291> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1291" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "From Livy it would appear that these Envoys were dispatched under the Consuls of 218 (Liv. 21.6.3), but as Saguntum fell before the winter of 219-218, and the arrival of the Envoys may well have preceded Hannibal's attack (Polyb. 3.15.4), the date is at the latest early in 219." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1245> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1245" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Ser. Sulpicius, in Gell. 4.3.2, cf. 17.21.44; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 44f., 118, 440f. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 38, no. 16." .
